          <LEXSenses>
            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2021-10-13 12:41:14" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>the state of being asleep</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>to sleep</Gloss>
                <Gloss>to be asleep</Gloss>
                <Gloss>sleep</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>In some languages sleep is expressed by an idiom, for example, ‘his soul had wandered away’ or ‘his eyes had disappeared.’ Though an expression such as ‘his soul had wandered away’ might appear in some languages to have misleading theological implications, it really means only ‘to sleep.’</Comments>
            </LEXSense>
          </LEXSenses>
